[Freezing does provide a measure of protection, except with arctic
strains of Trichinella. On the other hand American horses, whether
excess Mustangs on range or culled riding and work horses, go straight
from grazing to the slaughter house. It will be interesting to see
what impact this current problem has on the French demand for North
American horsemeat - Mod.MHJ
[Trichinellosis is henceforth banished from our list, as it is not an
emerging disease, just a signal of the failure of meat inspection
procedures. Now if a porcine TSE were to get into humans via horse
meat, that would be a different matter - Mod.JW
